<subSubSection id="21C4BAC2C6321B06FF6CF89DFD0AFE71" lastPageId="53" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6961E949C6321B07FF6CF89DFA19F80F" blockId="52.[151,1436,1798,2003]" box="[199,1436,1978,2003]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6321B07FF6CF89DFEBEF80E" bold="true" box="[199,315,1979,2003]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C6321B07FEEFF89CFDAFF80F" author="Collins, M. J. &amp; Jones, D. A. &amp; Clayton, D. A." box="[324,554,1978,2003]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="318 - 328" refId="ref46387" refString="Collins, M. J., Jones, D. A. &amp; Clayton, D. A. (1984) Redescription of Uca sindensis (Alcock, 1900) (Brachyura: Ocypodidae) with notes on the ecology of a population from Kuwait. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 4 (2), 318 - 328, figs. 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1984">
Collins 
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6321B07FE36F89DFE4AF80E" box="[413,463,1979,2003]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">et al</emphasis>
. (1984)
</bibRefCitation>
recorded this species from 
<collectingCountry id="11C9A9D9C6321B07FCC3F89DFC10F80F" box="[872,917,1979,2002]" name="Iran" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Iran</collectingCountry>
in the northern Persian Gulf. 
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C6321B07FB46F89CFA19F80F" author="Apel, M. &amp; Turkay, M." box="[1261,1436,1978,2002]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="131 - 142" refId="ref45263" refString="Apel, M., &amp; Turkay, M. (1999) Taxonomic Composition, Distribution and Zoogeographic Relationships of the Grapsid and Ocypodid Crab Fauna of Intertidal Soft Bottoms in the Persian Gulf. Estuarine, Coastal and Shelf Science, 49 (Supplement A), 131 - 142" type="journal article" year="1999">Apel &amp; Türkay</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6961E949C6331B06FF3CFFB1FD0AFE71" blockId="53.[151,1436,151,428]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
(1999) mentioned that the specimen recorded by 
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C6331B06FD4EFFB1FC5DFF72" author="Collins, M. J. &amp; Jones, D. A. &amp; Clayton, D. A." box="[741,984,151,176]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="318 - 328" refId="ref46387" refString="Collins, M. J., Jones, D. A. &amp; Clayton, D. A. (1984) Redescription of Uca sindensis (Alcock, 1900) (Brachyura: Ocypodidae) with notes on the ecology of a population from Kuwait. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 4 (2), 318 - 328, figs. 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1984">
Collins 
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6331B06FCE8FFBFFCFFFF6D" box="[835,890,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">et al</emphasis>
. (1984)
</bibRefCitation>
was deposited in the Natural History Museum of London is actually from the Gulf of 
<collectingCountry id="11C9A9D9C6331B06FD12FF9AFC84FF09" box="[697,769,188,212]" name="Oman" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Oman</collectingCountry>
. Beinlich &amp; von Hagen (2006) introduced a new subgenus, namely 
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6331B06FF5BFFC6FED7FF25" box="[240,338,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Cranuca</emphasis>
for this species which is considered of being part of an ancestral base for wide-front fiddler crabs which is characterized by combining a wide front and lacking a pleonal clasping apparatus. This species is common in the Red Sea, living sympatrically with 
<taxonomicName id="AEDE92CAC6331B06FDC3FE0FFC83FE9D" baseAuthorityName="Kossmann" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[616,774,296,320]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Uca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albimana">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6331B06FDC3FE0FFC83FE9D" box="[616,774,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Uca albimana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
along muddy shores and mangroves. Both of these species have been recorded from the south-western Persian Gulf along the coast of the 
<collectingCountry id="11C9A9D9C6331B06FBB1FE6AFBD6FEB9" box="[1050,1107,332,356]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">UAE</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C6331B06FBC8FE6AFAD3FEB9" author="Apel, M. &amp; Turkay, M." box="[1123,1366,332,356]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="131 - 142" refId="ref45263" refString="Apel, M., &amp; Turkay, M. (1999) Taxonomic Composition, Distribution and Zoogeographic Relationships of the Grapsid and Ocypodid Crab Fauna of Intertidal Soft Bottoms in the Persian Gulf. Estuarine, Coastal and Shelf Science, 49 (Supplement A), 131 - 142" type="journal article" year="1999">Apel &amp; Türkay 1999</bibRefCitation>
). This record shows that 
<taxonomicName id="AEDE92CAC6331B06FEC8FE57FE52FE5A" baseAuthorityName="Hoffman" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[355,471,368,392]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Uca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inversa">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6331B06FEC8FE57FEF2FE55" box="[355,375,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">U</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6331B06FE2EFE56FE52FE5A" box="[389,471,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">inversa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distributed northward, now colonizing in 
<collectingCountry id="11C9A9D9C6331B06FC04FE49FC7BFE5A" box="[943,1022,367,391]" name="Iran" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Qeshm</collectingCountry>
I., whereas 
<taxonomicName id="AEDE92CAC6331B06FB2CFE57FA96FE55" baseAuthorityName="Kossmann" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[1159,1299,368,392]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ocypodidae" genus="Uca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albimana">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6331B06FB2CFE57FB1EFE55" box="[1159,1179,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">U</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6331B06FB02FE56FA96FE55" box="[1193,1299,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">albimana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the south-western part of the Persian Gulf.
</paragraph>
